<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-946] [docs] Using Log4j 2 in Web Applications: Update example (Log4jWebLifeCycle is not visible)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-946</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On the &lt;a href=&quot;http://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/webapp.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/webapp.html&lt;/a&gt; page you mention following code snippet:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; Log4jWebLifeCycle webLifeCycle =     WebLoggerContextUtils.getWebLifeCycle(TestAsyncServlet.&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.getServletContext());
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The problem is, Log4jWebLifeCycle is package-private and you can&apos;t use it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
